Gabite

Rough Skin

Passive Ability

When damaged by a nearby opposing Melee Pokémon, reflects 30% of the damage received back to that opposing Pokémon as Attack-based damage (2s CD).

Attack

Auto Attack

Gains 1 stack toward boosted attacks after hitting an auto attack or move, stacking up to 5 times. At 5 stacks, all basic attacks become boosted attacks with increased attack speed and additional 20% lifesteal, dealing increased damage to opposing Pokémon, and dealing an additional 10% remaining HP damage to them. All stacks decay after 4s of not hitting an auto attack or move.

Against wild Pokémon: basic attack damage is capped at 1000; boosted attack damage is capped at 1100; additional remaining HP damage is capped at 350.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

120% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

0% Atk + 3 x (Level - 1) + 28

Sand Attack

Move 1

6.00s Debuff

The user hurls sand in the designated direction, reducing the field of vision of opposing Pokémon by 50% and decreasing their movement speed by 20% for 2s; increasing the user's movement speed by 30% for 2s and auto attack speed by 30% for 3s when this move hits.

Sand Attack Upgrade Choices

Dig

8.00s Dash

The user digs underground, becoming untargetable while underground, and dashes quickly forward. The user then jumps out from underground beneath the first opposing Pokémon hit, after traveling max distance, or when coming into contact with an unpassable wall, increasing the user's Defense and Sp. Def for 3s, dealing damage to nearby opposing Pokémon and throwing them for 0.5s.

130% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 240

0% Atk + 25 x (Level - 1) + 25

Strengthens the duration of the throw to 1s.

Dragon Rush

5.50s Dash

The user jumps back and briefly channels, reducing damage received by 30% for 0.9s, and dives forward, dragging all enemies within a small radius to the designated location, then damaging nearby opposing Pokémon afterward.

The user can use Dragon Claw during the first half of the channel to add the Dragon Claw hits as a combo attack. This combo attack scoops up opposing Pokémon, dealing damage with both Dragon Rush and Dragon Claw's first attack and stunning them. If the combo attack hits, the user then throws opposing Pokémon back down with the second Dragon Claw attack, dealing damage with a strengthened slow.

121% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 200

Becomes unstoppable during this move; this includes the combo attack with Dragon Claw.

Bulldoze

Move 2

5.00s Area

The user stomps down on the ground, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect.

145% Atk + 13 x (Level - 1) + 240

Bulldoze Upgrade Choices

Earthquake

7.00s Area

The user jumps up and crashes forcefully to the ground, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and decreasing their movement speed by 20% for 2s. Two aftershocks follow the initial crash, dealing less damage to opposing Pokémon in the area of effect.

125% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 195

63.5% Atk + 7 x (Level - 1) + 97

Strengthens the movement speed decrease of opposing Pokémon near the center of the crash to 40%.

Dragon Claw

4.00s Melee

The user charges in the designated direction viciously and attacks with two claw swipes. The first attack damages opposing Pokémon and shoves them in the designated direction. The second attack deals more damage to opposing Pokémon and decreases their movement speed by 45% for 2s.

When this move is used in a combo attack with Dragon Rush, the movement speed decrease on the second attack is strengthened to 60% for 2s.

88% Atk + 6 x (Level - 1) + 155

108% Atk + 7 x (Level - 1) + 188

Increases the damage of both attacks.

106% Atk + 6 x (Level - 1) + 170

127.2% Atk + 7 x (Level - 1) + 204

Livid Outrage

Unite Move

112s 100000 Melee

Unlocks at level 9

The user goes berserk, becoming unstoppable and receiving 30% reduced damage for 5s while unleashing five powerful attacks in a row. The user dashes forward and damages opposing Pokémon in a unique designated area with each attack, taking a brief moment after each attack to aim the next dash. Every attack more damage than the last. The fifth attack throws opposing Pokémon hit and decreases their movement speed by 30% for 1s. The user is left confused for 0.5s afterward.

227% Atk + 10 x (Level - 1) + 330

267% Atk + 11 x (Level - 1) + 450

307% Atk + 12 x (Level - 1) + 570

307% Atk + 13 x (Level - 1) + 920

307% Atk + 14 x (Level - 1) + 1270

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 30% Max HP Shield
